        <p className="mb-4">As a truck driver or owner-operator, navigating the complexities of the International Fuel Tax Agreement (IFTA) is a crucial part of staying compliant and keeping your rig on the road. IFTA allows interstate carriers to report fuel taxes to a single base jurisdiction, simplifying the process of paying fuel taxes across multiple states and provinces. Renewing your IFTA license and decals is an annual task, and understanding the process is key to avoiding penalties and delays. This step-by-step guide will walk you through the IFTA renewal process, ensuring you're prepared and compliant.</p>

